🕵️ Troubleshooting the "IO Path" with crictl

When a bank transaction fails due to storage, you troubleshoot in reverse:

    Is the Bit there? Check the Storage Array logs for "SENSE" errors or failed disks.

    Is the Path there? Use multipath -ll on the host to see if one of the FC/iSCSI paths is down.

    Is the Mount there? Use sudo crictl inspect <id> | jq .info.runtimeSpec.mounts to see if the container is looking at the right device.

    Is the App writing? Use sudo nsenter -t <pid> -m iostat -xz 1 to watch real-time disk utilization inside the pod.
